IDENTIFICATION: We consulted descriptions and measurements of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D1BFFACFFA4EA3A11BEFE7C538F" authorityName="Handley" authorityYear="1960" box="[343,502,1440,1463]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="44" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="riparius">
<emphasis id="B90EEA8AFFACFFA4EA3A11BEFE7C538F" box="[343,502,1440,1463]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="44">Myotis riparius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
provided by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEB4B69FFACFFA4EB0111DCFE9953E2" author="Handley, C. O., Jr." box="[108,275,1474,1498]" pageId="44" pageNumber="44" pagination="459 - 479" refId="ref36876" refString="Handley, C. O., Jr. 1960. Descriptions of new bats from Panama. Proceedings of the United States National Museum 113: 459 - 479." type="journal article" year="1960">Handley (1960)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEB4B69FFACFFA4EA7111DCFE2D53E2" author="LaVal, R. K." box="[284,423,1474,1498]" pageId="44" pageNumber="44" pagination="1 - 54" refId="ref38194" refString="LaVal, R. K. 1973. A revision of the Neotropical bats of the genus Myotis. Bulletin of the Natural History Museum of Los Angeles County 15: 1 - 54." type="journal article" year="1973">LaVal (1973)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEB4B69FFACFFA4EADC11DCFF3E53C4" author="Simmons, N. B. &amp; R. S. Voss" pageId="44" pageNumber="44" pagination="1 - 219" refId="ref42345" refString="Simmons, N. B., and R. S. Voss. 1998. The mammals of Paracou, French Guiana: a Neotropical lowland rainforest fauna. Part 1. Bats. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 237: 1 - 219." type="journal article" year="1998">Simmons and Voss (1998)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEB4B69FFACFFA4EBAF11FBFDF253C4" author="Brosset, A. &amp; P. Charles-Dominique" box="[194,632,1508,1532]" pageId="44" pageNumber="44" pagination="509 - 560" refId="ref33466" refString="Brosset, A., and P. Charles-Dominique. 1990. The bats from French Guiana: a taxonomic, faunistic and ecological approach. Mammalia 54: 509 - 560." type="journal article" year="1990">Brosset and Charles-Dominique (1990)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEB4B69FFACFFA4EB011219FE365027" author="Lopez-Gonzalez, C. &amp; S. J. Presely &amp; R. D. Owen &amp; M. R. Willig" box="[108,444,1543,1567]" pageId="44" pageNumber="44" pagination="138 - 160" refId="ref38844" refString="Lopez-Gonzalez, C., S. J. Presely, R. D. Owen, and M. R. Willig. 2001. Taxonomic status of Myotis (Chiroptera: Vespertilionidae) in Paraguay. Journal of Mammalogy 82: 138 - 160." type="journal article" year="2001">López-González et al. (2001)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEB4B69FFACFFA4EAA31219FF3E5079" author="Moratelli, R. &amp; A. L. Gardner &amp; J. A. de Oliveira &amp; D. E. Wilson" pageId="44" pageNumber="44" pagination="1 - 36" refId="ref39946" refString="Moratelli, R., A. L. Gardner, J. A. de Oliveira, and D. E. Wilson. 2013. Review of Myotis (Chiroptera, Vespertilionidae) from northern South America, including description of a new species. American Museum Novitates 3780: 1 - 36." type="journal article" year="2013">Moratelli et al. (2013)</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEB4B69FFACFFA4EB991237FE5E5079" author="Novaes, R. L. M. &amp; R. F. Souza &amp; R. Moratelli" box="[244,468,1577,1601]" pageId="44" pageNumber="44" pagination="51 - 56" refId="ref40225" refString="Novaes, R. L. M., R. F. Souza, and R. Moratelli. 2017. Myotis riparius (Chiroptera: Vespertilionidae). Mammalian Species 946: 51 - 56." type="journal article" year="2017">Novaes et al. (2017)</bibRefCitation>
. No subspecies are currently recognized in 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D1BFFACFFA4EAFD1252FF5850BE" authority="(Novaes et al., 2017)" baseAuthorityName="Novaes" baseAuthorityYear="2017" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="44" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="riparius">
<emphasis id="B90EEA8AFFACFFA4EAFD1252FD8F505B" box="[400,517,1612,1635]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="44">M. riparius</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFEB4B69FFACFFA4E97E1255FF4650BE" author="Novaes, R. L. M. &amp; R. F. Souza &amp; R. Moratelli" pageId="44" pageNumber="44" pagination="51 - 56" refId="ref40225" refString="Novaes, R. L. M., R. F. Souza, and R. Moratelli. 2017. Myotis riparius (Chiroptera: Vespertilionidae). Mammalian Species 946: 51 - 56." type="journal article" year="2017">Novaes et al., 2017</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Our Mayo River basin voucher specimens exhibit the diagnostic characteristics of the species: fur long and woolly; dorsal pelage unicol- ored; plagiopatagium attached to the foot at the level of the base of the toes; a fringe of hairs lacking along the trailing edge of uropatagium; sagittal and lambdoidal crests present; and occipital region flattened posteriorly (
<bibRefCitation id="EFEB4B69FFACFFA4E88D1574FB3B57BA" author="Novaes, R. L. M. &amp; R. F. Souza &amp; R. Moratelli" box="[992,1201,362,386]" pageId="44" pageNumber="44" pagination="51 - 56" refId="ref40225" refString="Novaes, R. L. M., R. F. Souza, and R. Moratelli. 2017. Myotis riparius (Chiroptera: Vespertilionidae). Mammalian Species 946: 51 - 56." type="journal article" year="2017">Novaes et al., 2017</bibRefCitation>
). Measurements of the Mayo River specimens fall within the range of measurements reported for the species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
